==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Markov process
<hw>Mark"ov pro`cess</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[after
<person>A. A. <etsep>Markov</etsep></person>, Russian mathematician, b.
1856, d. 1922.]</ety> <fld>(Statistics)</fld> <def>a random process in
which the probabilities of states in a series depend only on the
properties of the immediately preceding state or the next preceding
state, independent of the path by which the preceding state was reached.
It is distinguished from a <contr>Markov chain</contr> in that the
states of a <ex>Markov process</ex> may be continuous as well as
discrete.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>Markoff
process</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marksman</ent>⟦br⟧
